The people's court shall terminate the enforcement in the following cases:
(1) The applicant withdraws the application;
(2) The legal document on which the enforcement is based is revoked;
(3) The citizen who is the subject of enforcement dies without assets to be executed and without any obligation to bear;
(4) The right holder in a case of claiming alimony, support fees, or childcare fees dies;
(5) The citizen who is the subject of enforcement is unable to repay the loan due to living difficulties, has no source of income, and has lost the ability to work;
(6) Other circumstances in which the people's court considers it necessary to terminate the enforcement.

People's courts can use the following methods to serve legal documents on parties who do not have a domicile within the territory of the People's Republic of China:

(1) Serve according to the methods specified in international treaties concluded or jointly participated in by the country where the person to be served is located and the People's Republic of China; 
(2) Serve through diplomatic channels; 
(3) For recipients with Chinese nationality, serve through the Chinese embassy or consulate in the country where the recipient is located; 
(4) Serve on the legal representative authorized by the recipient to accept service; 
(5) Serve on the representative organization established within the territory of the People's Republic of China by the recipient or on the branch or business agent authorized to accept service; 
(6) If the recipient's country allows service by postal delivery, the documents may be sent by mail. If three months have passed since the date of mailing and the service of delivery receipt has not been returned, but it can be determined that the documents have been served based on various circumstances, the service shall be deemed to have been made on the date of expiry; 
(7) Serve by fax, email, or other methods that can confirm that the recipient has received the documents; 
(8) If none of the above methods can be used, serve by public announcement. Service shall be deemed to have been made on the date three months after the date of announcement.

