Public property referred to in this Law refers to the following:
(1) State-owned property;
(2) Property collectively owned by the laboring masses;
(3) Property donated by society for poverty alleviation and other public welfare undertakings, as well as property held in special funds.
Private property managed, used, or transported by state organs, state-owned companies, enterprises, collective enterprises, and people's organizations shall be treated as public property.

The private property owned by citizens, as referred to in this law, includes the following:

(1) Legitimate income, savings, housing, and other living materials of citizens;
(2) Production means owned by individuals and families in accordance with the law;
(3) Legitimate property of individual businesses and private enterprises;
(4) Stocks, shares, bonds, and other properties owned by individuals in accordance with the law.

According to this law, "serious injury" refers to any of the following injuries:
(1) Causing permanent disability of limbs or disfigurement of a person;
(2) Causing the loss of hearing, vision, or other organ functions of a person;
(3) Other injuries that have significant impact on personal health.

According to law, if a designated or determined firearm manufacturing or sales company violates firearm management regulations and engages in any of the following behaviors, the unit shall be fined, and the directly responsible managerial personnel and other directly responsible individuals shall be sentenced to imprisonment for up to five years. If the circumstances are serious, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than five years but less than ten years. If the circumstances are particularly serious, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than ten years or life imprisonment:
(1) Manufacturing or distributing firearms exceeding the quota or not in accordance with the prescribed types, with the purpose of illegal sales;
(2) Manufacturing firearms without serial numbers, with duplicate numbers, or with fake numbers, with the purpose of illegal sales;
(3) Illegally selling firearms or selling firearms manufactured for export within the territory.

The following behaviors shall be punished as smuggling crimes in accordance with the relevant regulations in this section:
(1) Directly purchasing prohibited imported goods from smugglers, or directly purchasing other goods from smugglers that are smuggled into the country, in large amounts;
(2) Transporting, purchasing, or selling prohibited imported or exported goods in the internal or territorial waters, or transporting, purchasing, or selling restricted imported or exported goods in large amounts without legal certification;
(3) Evading customs supervision by importing solid waste from overseas into the country.

For staff members of state-owned companies, enterprises, and public institutions who take advantage of their positions and cause significant losses to national interests, the following penalties apply: imprisonment for up to three years or detention, along with a fine; for causing particularly significant losses to national interests, imprisonment for more than three years but less than seven years, along with a fine:

(1) Entrusting profitable business operations of their own units to their relatives or friends;
(2) Purchasing goods from units managed by their relatives or friends at prices significantly higher than the market price or selling goods to units managed by their relatives or friends at prices significantly lower than the market price;
(3) Purchasing substandard goods from units managed by their relatives or friends.

Note: This is a rough translation and may not be completely accurate.

If the managing personnel of state-owned companies, enterprises, or their superior authorities engage in embezzlement and sell state-owned assets at a low price or at a discounted rate, causing significant losses to the national interests, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for less than three years or detained; if the losses to the national interests are particularly significant, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for three to seven years.

Directors, supervisors, and senior management personnel of listed companies who violate their fiduciary duties to the company and use their positions to manipulate the company shall be sentenced to imprisonment for less than three years or detained, and may also be fined if their actions cause significant damage to the company's interests; if their actions cause particularly significant losses to the company's interests, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for three to seven years and fined.

The following actions are considered as manipulation:
(1) Providing funds, goods, services, or other assets to other entities or individuals without compensation;
(2) Providing or accepting funds, goods, services, or other assets under obviously unfair conditions;
(3) Providing funds, goods, services, or other assets to entities or individuals with obvious insolvency;
(4) Providing guarantees to entities or individuals with obvious insolvency without justified reasons, or providing guarantees to other entities or individuals without justified reasons;
(5) Waiving claims or assuming debts without justified reasons;
(6) Damaging the interests of the listed company through other means.

If the controlling shareholder or actual controller of a listed company instigates the directors, supervisors, or senior management personnel of the listed company to commit the above-mentioned actions, they shall be punished in accordance with the provisions of the preceding paragraph.

If a listed company commits the crimes stated above, its legal representative or person in charge shall be sentenced to criminal liability.

Anyone who counterfeits currency shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of more than three years but less than ten years, and shall be fined with an amount ranging from fifty thousand yuan to five hundred thousand yuan; anyone who commits any of the following circumstances shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of over ten years, life imprisonment, or death penalty, and shall be fined with an amount ranging from fifty thousand yuan to five hundred thousand yuan, or have their property confiscated:
(1) The ringleader of a counterfeit currency group;
(2) Counterfeiting currency with an especially large amount;
(3) Any other particularly serious circumstances.
以上内容翻译为英文:

Anyone who forges or alters financial instruments shall be sentenced to imprisonment for up to five years or detention, and shall also be fined between twenty thousand and two hundred thousand yuan. In cases of severe circumstances, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than five years but less than ten years, and shall also be fined between fifty thousand and five hundred thousand yuan. In cases of particularly serious circumstances, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than ten years or life imprisonment, and shall also be fined between fifty thousand and five hundred thousand yuan or have their property confiscated. The following circumstances are included:

(1) Forging or altering bills of exchange, promissory notes, or checks;
(2) Forging or altering entrusted collection vouchers, remittance vouchers, bank deposit certificates, or other banking settlement certificates;
(3) Forging or altering letters of credit or accompanying documents and files;
(4) Forging credit cards.

For offenses committed by organizations, the organization shall be fined, and the directly responsible managers and other personnel shall be punished in accordance with the above provisions.

Anyone who engages in activities that disrupt credit card management shall be sentenced to imprisonment for up to three years or detention, and shall also be fined between ten thousand and one hundred thousand yuan. In cases of large quantities or other serious circumstances, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than three years but less than ten years, and shall also be fined between twenty thousand and two hundred thousand yuan. The following circumstances are included:

(1) Knowingly possessing or transporting forged credit cards or a large quantity of blank forged credit cards;
(2) Illegally possessing a large quantity of other persons' credit cards;
(3) Using false identification to fraudulently obtain credit cards;
(4) Selling, purchasing, or providing others with forged credit cards or credit cards obtained through false identification.

In one of the following situations, if the circumstances are severe, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not more than five years or criminal detention, and shall also be fined; if the circumstances are particularly severe, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than five years but not more than ten years, and shall also be fined:

(1) Acting alone or in collusion, manipulating the securities or futures trading prices or volumes by combining funds advantages, shareholding or contract holding advantages, or information advantages;

(2) Colluding with others to conduct securities or futures trading with pre-agreed time, price, and method, and affecting the securities or futures trading prices or volumes;

(3) Conducting securities trading between one's own controlled accounts or conducting self-trading of futures contracts as the trading counterpart, and affecting the securities or futures trading prices or volumes;

(4) Manipulating the securities or futures markets by other means. 

If a unit commits the crime stated in the preceding paragraph, it shall be fined, and the directly responsible person in charge and other directly responsible personnel shall be punished according to the provisions in the preceding paragraph.

For acts related to the concealment or disguise of proceeds and income derived from drug crimes, organized crime activities, terrorist activities, smuggling crimes, corruption and bribery crimes, disruption of financial management order, and financial fraud crimes, where the nature of the crimes is known, the following penalties shall apply: confiscation of the proceeds and income generated from the commission of the above crimes, imprisonment for up to five years or detention, and a fine of not less than 5% but not more than 20% of the amount involved in money laundering; if the circumstances are serious, imprisonment for more than five years but less than ten years, and a fine of not less than 5% but not more than 20% of the amount involved in money laundering. 

The following acts shall be subject to the aforementioned penalties for concealing or disguising the source and nature of the proceeds and income:

(1) Providing funding accounts;
(2) Assisting in converting assets into cash, financial instruments, or securities;
(3) Assisting in the transfer of funds through transfers or other settlement methods;
(4) Assisting in the remittance of funds overseas;
(5) Concealing or disguising the source and nature of the proceeds and income in any other method.

If a unit commits the aforementioned offense, it shall be fined, and the directly responsible persons in charge and other directly responsible personnel shall be sentenced to imprisonment for up to five years or detention. 

Section 5 Financial Fraud Crimes.

One of the following circumstances, with the purpose of illegal possession, defrauds a large amount of loans from banks or other financial institutions: shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment or detention of not more than five years, and fined not less than twenty thousand yuan but not more than two hundred thousand yuan; for huge amounts or other serious circumstances, shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than five years but not more than ten years, and fined not less than fifty thousand yuan but not more than five hundred thousand yuan; for particularly huge amounts or other particularly serious circumstances, shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than ten years or life imprisonment, and fined not less than fifty thousand yuan but not more than five hundred thousand yuan or confiscation of property:

(1) Creating false reasons for introducing funds, projects, etc.;
(2) Using false economic contracts;
(3) Using false certificates;
(4) Using false property certificates as collateral or repeatedly guaranteeing beyond the value of the mortgaged property;
(5) Defrauding loans through other methods.

One of the following circumstances, engaging in fraudulent financial bill activities, with a significant amount involved, shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not more than five years or criminal detention, and shall also be fined not less than 20,000 yuan but not more than 200,000 yuan; if the amount is huge or there are other serious circumstances, shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than five years but not more than ten years, and shall also be fined not less than 50,000 yuan but not more than 500,000 yuan; if the amount is particularly huge or there are other particularly serious circumstances, shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than ten years or life imprisonment, and shall also be fined not less than 50,000 yuan but not more than 500,000 yuan or have their property confiscated:

(1) Using counterfeit or altered promissory notes, bills, or checks, with knowledge of their falsity;
(2) Using invalidated promissory notes, bills, or checks, with knowledge of their invalidity;
(3) Assuming the identity of others with their promissory notes, bills, or checks;
(4) Issuing blank checks or checks with mismatched reserved seals, and deceiving for the purpose of obtaining property;
(5) Issuing promissory notes or bills without financial guarantees or making false records at the time of issuance, for the purpose of deceiving for property.

The provisions of the preceding paragraph shall apply to the use of counterfeit or altered bank settlement vouchers, remittance vouchers, bank deposit certificates, and other bank settlement vouchers.

