If any of the following circumstances occur, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not more than five years or criminal detention, and shall also be fined an amount ranging from 20,000 yuan to 200,000 yuan: if the amount involved is substantial or there are other serious circumstances, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than five years but not more than ten years, and fined an amount ranging from 50,000 yuan to 500,000 yuan; if the amount involved is particularly large or there are other particularly serious circumstances, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than ten years or life imprisonment, and fined an amount ranging from 50,000 yuan to 500,000 yuan or confiscation of property:

(1) Using counterfeit or altered letters of credit or associated documents or papers;
(2) Using invalid letters of credit;
(3) Obtaining letters of credit through deception;
(4) Engaging in letter of credit fraud by other means.

For any of the following circumstances involving credit card fraud activities with significant amounts, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment of up to five years or detention, along with a fine ranging from 20,000 to 200,000 yuan; for cases involving large amounts or other serious circumstances, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment of five to ten years, along with a fine ranging from 50,000 to 500,000 yuan; for cases involving extremely large amounts or other particularly serious circumstances, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment of more than ten years or life imprisonment, along with a fine ranging from 50,000 to 500,000 yuan or confiscation of property:

(1) Using counterfeit credit cards or credit cards obtained by fraudulent identity proofs;
(2) Using invalidated credit cards;
(3) Impersonating others and using their credit cards;
(4) Willfully overdrawing credit limits for illegal possession and failing to repay after being urged by the issuing bank.

The theft of credit cards and their use shall be punished according to the provisions of Article 264 of this law.

