Anyone who commits insurance fraud in one of the following situations, with a significant amount involved, shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of no more than five years or detention, and shall also be fined between ten thousand and one hundred thousand yuan; if the amount is huge or there are other serious circumstances, the person shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of no less than five years and no more than ten years, and be fined between twenty thousand and two hundred thousand yuan; if the amount is particularly huge or there are other particularly serious circumstances, the person shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of no less than ten years, and be fined between twenty thousand and two hundred thousand yuan or have their property confiscated:

(1) The insured intentionally fabricates the insured subject and cheats to obtain insurance money;
(2) The insured, the policyholder, or the beneficiary fabricates false reasons for the insurance accident or exaggerates the extent of the loss to cheat and obtain insurance money;
(3) The insured, the policyholder, or the beneficiary fabricates a non-existent insurance accident to cheat and obtain insurance money;
(4) The insured, the policyholder intentionally causes a property loss insurance accident to cheat and obtain insurance money;
(5) The insured, the beneficiary intentionally causes the death, disability, or illness of the insured person to cheat and obtain insurance money.

If the acts mentioned in the previous paragraph (item 4 and item 5) also constitute other crimes, they shall be punished according to the provisions on cumulative punishment for multiple crimes.

If a unit commits the crimes in the first paragraph, the unit shall be fined, and the directly responsible personnel in charge and other directly responsible personnel shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of no more than five years or detention; if the amount is huge or there are other serious circumstances, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of no less than five years and no more than ten years; if the amount is particularly huge or there are other particularly serious circumstances, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of no less than ten years.

Any appraiser, witness, or property evaluator who intentionally commits the above acts shall be punished according to the provisions above.

For-profit purposes, if any of the following circumstances constitute infringement of copyright and the amount of illegal gains is large or there are other serious circumstances, the person shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of less than three years or criminal detention, and shall also be fined or solely fined. If the amount of illegal gains is enormous or there are other particularly serious circumstances, the person shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of more than three years but less than seven years, and shall also be fined:

(1) Copying and distributing textual works, music, films, television programs, video works, computer software, and other works without the permission of the copyright holder;

(2) Publishing books that others have exclusive publishing rights to;

(3) Copying and distributing audio or video recordings without the permission of the producer;

(4) Producing and selling counterfeit art works with another person's signature.

In one of the following circumstances, with the purpose of illegal possession, if someone deceives the other party to the contract and obtains a large amount of property during the process of signing and performing the contract, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for not more than three years or fixed-term detention, and shall also be fined. If the amount is huge or there are other serious circumstances, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than three years but not more than ten years, and shall be fined. If the amount is exceptionally huge or there are other particularly serious circumstances, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than ten years or life imprisonment, and shall be fined or have their property confiscated:
(1) Signing a contract with a fictitious entity or impersonating another person;
(2) Using counterfeit, altered, or invalid bills or other false property certificates as guarantees;
(3) Without actual performance capacity, deceiving the other party to continue signing and performing the contract by first performing a small amount of contract or partially performing the contract;
(4) After receiving the goods, payment, advance payment, or guarantee property from the other party, escaping;
(5) Deceiving the other party to obtain property by other means.

If someone organizes or leads pyramid selling activities under the pretext of promoting goods or providing services, requiring participants to pay fees or purchase goods or services to obtain membership, and forming a hierarchy in a certain order, directly or indirectly using the number of recruits as the basis for compensation or rebate, and enticing or coercing participants to continue recruiting others, deceiving property and disrupting the economic and social order, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for not more than five years or fixed-term detention, and shall also be fined. If the circumstances are serious, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than five years and shall be fined.

If the following illegal business activities violate national regulations and seriously disrupt the market order, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of less than five years or detention, and shall also be fined between one and five times the illegal gains; if the circumstances are particularly serious, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of more than five years, and shall be fined between one and five times the illegal gains or have their property confiscated:

(1) Operating exclusive or restricted commodities without permission as required by laws, regulations, or administrative rules;
(2) Dealing in import and export licenses, certificates of origin, or other business licenses or approval documents required by laws or administrative rules;
(3) Engaging in the illegal operation of securities, futures, insurance businesses without approval from the relevant authorities, or engaging in illegal fund payment settlement business;
(4) Other illegal business activities that seriously disrupt the market order.

If one of the following acts is committed by means of violence or threats, and the circumstances are serious, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment for not more than three years or detention, and shall also be fined or subject to a fine alone; if the circumstances are particularly serious, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than three years but not more than seven years, and shall also be fined.

(1) Forcibly buying or selling goods;
(2) Forcing others to provide or accept services;
(3) Forcing others to participate in or withdraw from bidding or auctions;
(4) Forcing others to transfer or acquire shares, bonds, or other assets of companies or enterprises;
(5) Forcing others to participate in or withdraw from specific business activities.

Trafficking in women and children shall be punished with imprisonment of not less than five years but not more than ten years, in addition to a fine. If any of the following circumstances exist, the offender shall be punished with imprisonment of not less than ten years or life imprisonment, in addition to a fine or confiscation of property. If the circumstances are particularly serious, the offender shall be sentenced to death, in addition to confiscation of property:

(1) Being the principal member of a group engaged in trafficking in women and children;
(2) Trafficking in three or more women or children;
(3) Raping the trafficked women;
(4) Inducing, coercing, or forcing the trafficked women into prostitution or selling them to others for forced prostitution;
(5) Kidnapping women or children by using violence, coercion, or drugging, with the purpose of selling them;
(6) Stealing infants and young children with the purpose of selling them;
(7) Causing severe injuries, death, or other serious consequences to the trafficked women, children, or their relatives;
(8) Selling women or children to foreign countries.

Trafficking in women and children refers to the act of deceiving, abducting, purchasing, selling, transporting, or transferring women or children for the purpose of sale.

