Those who rob public or private property by violence, coercion or other means shall be sentenced to imprisonment for not less than three years but not more than ten years, and shall also be fined; those who commit any of the following acts shall be sentenced to imprisonment for not less than ten years, life imprisonment or death, and shall also be fined or have their property confiscated:
(1) Robbery committed by entering a residence;
(2) Robbery committed on public transportation;
(3) Robbery committed at a bank or other financial institution;
(4) Multiple robberies or robberies involving a large amount of property;
(5) Robbery causing serious injury or death;
(6) Robbery committed by impersonating military or police personnel;
(7) Robbery committed with a firearm;
(8) Robbery of military supplies or disaster relief materials.

