Those who organize or actively participate in a group fight shall be sentenced to imprisonment for less than three years, detention, or control; those who are identified as primary culprits and actively participate in the fight shall be sentenced to imprisonment for more than three years but less than ten years if one of the following circumstances occurs: 
(1) Multiple incidents of group fights; 
(2) The group fight involves a large number of people and has a significant negative impact on society; 
(3) The group fight occurs in public places or key transportation routes, causing serious disorder to social order;
(4) The group fight involves the use of weapons.
If the group fight causes serious injuries or death, the offenders shall be punished according to the provisions in Article 234 and Article 232 of this Law.

Any of the following behaviors that disrupt social order shall be punished with imprisonment of no more than five years, detention, or surveillance:
(1) Assaulting others arbitrarily, with particularly malicious circumstances;
(2) Chasing, intercepting, insulting, or intimidating others, with particularly malicious circumstances;
(3) Forcibly taking or damaging public or private property, with serious circumstances;
(4) Causing serious disorder in public places by creating disturbances.
If multiple individuals are organized to carry out the above behaviors and seriously disrupt social order, they shall be sentenced to imprisonment of more than five years but not more than ten years, and may be fined.
