Criminals who are lawfully detained, if found guilty of one of the following acts which seriously disrupt the order of supervision, shall be sentenced to imprisonment of up to three years:

(1) Assaulting supervisory personnel;

(2) Organizing other detained individuals to disrupt the order of supervision;

(3) Participating in or inciting a disturbance to disrupt normal supervision order;

(4) Assaulting, physically punishing, or instigating others to assault or physically punish other detained individuals.

Anyone who organizes others to illegally cross the national (border) boundary shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of more than two years but not more than seven years, and shall also be fined. In any of the following circumstances, the person shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of more than seven years or life imprisonment, and shall also be fined or have their property confiscated: 
(1) The principal members of a group that organizes others to illegally cross the national (border) boundary;
(2) Multiple instances of organizing others to illegally cross the national (border) boundary or organizing a large number of people to do so;
(3) Causing serious injury or death to the people being organized;
(4) Depriving or restricting the personal freedom of the people being organized;
(5) Resisting inspection by violent or threatening means;
(6) Obtaining a substantial amount of illegal proceeds;
(7) Other particularly serious circumstances.
If the crime in the preceding paragraph is committed and results in the killing, injury, rape, trafficking, or other criminal acts against the people being organized, or the killing or injury of inspection personnel, the person shall be punished according to the provisions on concurrent offenses.

Anyone who transports others to illegally cross the national (border) boundary shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment, criminal detention, or control for less than five years, and shall also be fined. If any of the following circumstances exist, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of five to ten years, and shall also be fined:

(1) Repeatedly engaging in transportation or transporting a large number of people;
(2) Using transportation vehicles such as ships and vehicles that do not have the necessary safety conditions, causing serious consequences;
(3) Obtaining a huge amount of illegal proceeds;
(4) Having other particularly serious circumstances.

If the act of transporting others to illegally cross the national (border) boundary causes serious injury or death to the transported person, or if violence or threatening methods are used to resist inspection, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than seven years, and shall also be fined.

If the offenses stated in the first two paragraphs are committed, resulting in the killing, injury, rape, abduction, or other crimes against the transported person, or the killing or injury of inspection personnel, the offender shall be punished in accordance with the provisions on cumulative punishment.

