The theft and excavation of ancient cultural sites and tombs that possess historical, artistic, and scientific value shall be punished with imprisonment for a term of not less than three years but not more than ten years, and a fine; if the circumstances are relatively minor, the punishment shall be imprisonment for a term of not more than three years, detention, or control, and a fine; if any of the following circumstances exist, the punishment shall be imprisonment for a term of not less than ten years or life imprisonment, and a fine or confiscation of property:

(1) The excavation of cultural sites and tombs that have been identified as national key cultural heritage sites or provincial-level cultural heritage sites;

(2) The key individuals in groups engaged in the excavation of cultural sites and tombs;

(3) Multiple instances of excavation of cultural sites and tombs;

(4) The excavation of cultural sites and tombs, accompanied by the theft or serious damage of valuable cultural relics.

The excavation of scientifically valuable ancient human fossils and vertebrate fossils protected by the state shall be punished in accordance with the provisions of the preceding paragraph.

According to the provisions of the Law on the Prevention and Control of Infectious Diseases, if any of the following situations occur and cause the spread of a Class A infectious disease or pose a serious risk of transmission, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment for no more than three years or detention; if the consequences are particularly serious, the offender shall be sentenced to imprisonment for no less than three years but no more than seven years:

1. The drinking water supplied by water supply units does not meet the national hygiene standards;
2. Refusing to disinfect sewage, waste, and feces contaminated with pathogenic microorganisms in accordance with the hygiene requirements proposed by health and epidemic prevention institutions;
3. Permitting or condoning patients with infectious diseases, carriers of pathogens, and suspected patients to engage in work prohibited by the health administrative departments under the State Council that may lead to the spread of the infectious disease;
4. Refusing to implement the preventive and control measures proposed by health and epidemic prevention institutions in accordance with the Law on the Prevention and Control of Infectious Diseases.

If a unit commits the crime mentioned above, it shall be fined, and the directly responsible person in charge and other directly responsible personnel shall be punished in accordance with the provisions mentioned above.

The scope of Class A infectious diseases shall be determined in accordance with the Law of the People's Republic of China on the Prevention and Control of Infectious Diseases and relevant regulations of the State Council.

Smuggling, trafficking, transporting, and manufacturing drugs, regardless of the quantity, shall be subject to criminal liability and punishment.
Those who commit smuggling, trafficking, transporting, or manufacturing drugs under the following circumstances shall be sentenced to fifteen years' imprisonment, life imprisonment, or death penalty, and shall be confiscated of their properties:
(1) Smuggling, trafficking, transporting, or manufacturing one kilogram or more of opium, heroin, or methamphetamine, or a large quantity of other drugs;
(2) The ringleaders of drug smuggling, trafficking, transporting, or manufacturing groups;
(3) Those who arm themselves to protect drug smuggling, trafficking, transporting, or manufacturing activities;
(4) Those who use violence to resist inspection, detention, or arrest, with serious circumstances;
(5) Those involved in organized international drug trafficking activities.
Those who commit smuggling, trafficking, transporting, or manufacturing two hundred grams or more but less than one kilogram of opium, ten grams or more but less than fifty grams of heroin or methamphetamine, or a relatively large quantity of other drugs shall be sentenced to a minimum of seven years' imprisonment, along with a fine.
Those who commit smuggling, trafficking, transporting, or manufacturing less than two hundred grams of opium, less than ten grams of heroin or methamphetamine, or a small quantity of other drugs shall be sentenced to a maximum of three years' imprisonment, detention, or control, along with a fine; those with serious circumstances shall be sentenced to a minimum of three years and a maximum of seven years' imprisonment, along with a fine.
For enterprises that commit the offenses specified in the second, third, and fourth paragraphs, they shall be fined, and the persons directly in charge and other directly responsible personnel shall be punished according to the provisions of each paragraph.
For those who exploit or instigate minors to commit drug smuggling, trafficking, transporting, or manufacturing, or sell drugs to minors, heavier punishments shall be imposed.

Illegal planting of opium poppy, cannabis and other drugs. All plants shall be forcibly eradicated. If any of the following situations occurs, a penalty of imprisonment for up to five years, detention or control, along with a fine shall be imposed:
(1) Planting more than five hundred but less than three thousand opium poppy plants or a large quantity of other drug plants;
(2) Planting again after being dealt with by the public security organ;
(3) Resisting eradication.
Illegal planting of more than three thousand opium poppy plants or a large quantity of other drug plants shall be punished with imprisonment for more than five years, along with a fine or confiscation of property.
Illegal planting of opium poppy or other drug plants, if self-eradicated before harvesting, may be exempted from punishment.

Those who organize others to engage in prostitution or force others into prostitution shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of over five years but not more than ten years, with a fine imposed; if any of the following circumstances apply, they shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of over ten years, life imprisonment, or death, with a fine or confiscation of property imposed:

1. Organizing others to engage in prostitution, with serious circumstances;
2. Forcing girls under the age of fourteen to engage in prostitution;
3. Forcing multiple individuals into prostitution or forcing others into prostitution on multiple occasions;
4. Forcing victims into prostitution after committing rape;
5. Causing serious injuries, death, or other serious consequences to the victims of forced prostitution.

If any of the above circumstances are particularly severe, the perpetrator shall be sentenced to life imprisonment or death, with confiscation of property imposed.

Those who recruit, transport, or otherwise assist in organizing prostitution activities shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of less than five years, with a fine imposed; if the circumstances are serious, they shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of over five years but not more than ten years, with a fine imposed.

Types of administrative penalties:

(1) Warning;

(2) Fine;

(3) Confiscation of illegal gains and confiscation of illegally acquired property;

(4) Order to suspend production or business operation;

(5) Temporary suspension or revocation of license or permit;

(6) Administrative detention;

(7) Other administrative penalties as stipulated by laws and administrative regulations.

The entrusted organization must meet the following conditions:

(1) A public affairs organization established in accordance with the law;

(2) Staff members who are familiar with relevant laws, regulations, rules, and business operations;

(3) If technical inspections or technical appraisals are required for illegal acts, it should have the ability to organize corresponding technical inspections or technical appraisals.

Chapter 4 Jurisdiction and Application of Administrative Penalties

If a party involved meets any of the following circumstances, they should be given lenient or mitigated administrative penalties in accordance with the law:

(1) Taking the initiative to eliminate or reduce the harmful consequences of the illegal act;

(2) Being coerced by others to engage in illegal behavior;

(3) Cooperating with the administrative authority in investigating and dealing with illegal behavior, and showing meritorious performance;

(4) Other circumstances in which lenient or mitigated administrative penalties should be given in accordance with the law.

If the illegal act is minor and promptly corrected without causing any harmful consequences, no administrative penalty shall be imposed.

At the conclusion of the investigation, the head of the administrative authority shall review the investigation results and make the following decisions based on different circumstances:

(1) If there is a clear illegal act that warrants administrative penalties, a decision on administrative penalties shall be made based on the severity and specific circumstances of the case;

(2) If the illegal act is minor and can be exempt from administrative penalties according to the law, no administrative penalty shall be imposed;

(3) If the illegal facts cannot be established, no administrative penalty shall be imposed;

(4) If the illegal act constitutes a crime, it shall be transferred to the judicial authority.

In the case of complex or significant illegal acts, heavier administrative penalties shall be imposed, and the decision shall be made through collective discussions among the responsible persons of the administrative authority.

According to Article 38 of this Law, administrative organs shall make an administrative penalty decision in accordance with the provisions of this Law. The administrative penalty decision shall include the following:

1. The name or title and address of the party concerned;
2. The facts and evidence of the violation of laws, regulations, or rules;
3. The type and basis of the administrative penalty;
4. The method and deadline for the implementation of the administrative penalty;
5. The channels and deadline for applying for administrative reconsideration or filing administrative litigation against the administrative penalty decision;
6. The name of the administrative organ making the administrative penalty decision and the date of the decision.

The administrative penalty decision shall be affixed with the seal of the administrative organ making the administrative penalty decision.

According to Article 33 of this law, if one of the following circumstances occurs when making an administrative penalty decision on the spot, the law enforcement personnel may collect the fine on the spot:

(1) Imposing fines of twenty yuan or less in accordance with the law;

(2) Difficulties in executing the penalty after the event and unable to collect it on the spot.

Administrative organs shall implement administrative penalties. If any of the following circumstances occurs, the higher-level administrative organ or the relevant department shall order correction and may impose administrative sanctions on the directly responsible person in charge and other directly responsible persons according to law:

(1) There is no statutory basis for administrative penalties;

(2) Changing the type or extent of administrative penalties without authorization;

(3) Violating the statutory procedures for administrative penalties;

(4) Violating the provisions of Article 18 of this Law on delegated penalties.
